The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for decoding visual responses from EEG signals in ambulatory conditions. This involves addressing challenges such as movement artifacts and electromyography signals. The paper also focuses on the use of ear-EEG, which is a hardware issue. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of brain-computer interfaces, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper also discusses the validation of the signals with steady-state visual evoked potential, which falls under the sub-category cs.BIO (Computational Biology).
